Do not use your fingers.

251
00:39:06,377 --> 00:39:10,643
But if no one's looking, then you
can save the handkerchief.

252
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:15,750
Take care of your sweater,
now that I've mended it.

253
00:39:15,886 --> 00:39:20,255
If the teacher's wife invites you to
coffee, take only one piece cake.

254
00:39:20,558 --> 00:39:22,924
- But she won't.
- Why not?

255
00:39:23,060 --> 00:39:26,860
- He never got married.
- I see.

256
00:39:26,997 --> 00:39:28,259
Run along now.

257
00:39:32,837 --> 00:39:37,035
B-A is ba.
B- E is be.

258
00:39:37,641 --> 00:39:42,601
B-A is ba.

259
00:39:42,813 --> 00:39:47,147
B- E is be.

260
00:39:47,318 --> 00:39:51,084
B- I is bi.

261
00:39:51,255 --> 00:39:54,349
B-O is bo.

262
00:39:54,492 --> 00:39:57,825
B- U is bu.

263
00:39:58,162 --> 00:40:01,654
B-Y is by.

264
00:40:02,366 --> 00:40:06,268
B-A is bahh!

265
00:40:06,404 --> 00:40:09,771
You miserable brats.
Will you be quiet?!

266
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:12,272
Quiet, you rascals!

267
00:40:23,287 --> 00:40:25,346
Quiet! Quiet!

268
00:40:25,956 --> 00:40:27,184
You rascals!

269
00:40:33,130 --> 00:40:36,588
Let us welcome the new pupil.

270
00:40:40,471 --> 00:40:42,063
Stand up.

271
00:40:43,574 --> 00:40:47,169
- Tell us your name.
- Pelle Karlsson.

272
00:40:49,146 --> 00:40:50,841
And what can you do?

273
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:55,680
I can hit a cow with a stone
from a hundred paces.

274
00:40:57,221 --> 00:41:00,987
And I can make my cows stand still
by buzzing like a wasp.

275
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,958
- And I can make Bismarck...
- Can you read?

276
00:41:04,128 --> 00:41:06,289
No, otherwise I wouldn't be here.

277
00:41:08,299 --> 00:41:11,462
Leave your impudent
remarks at home.

278
00:41:23,948 --> 00:41:28,214
What's this one, Pelle?
Don't think I've ever seen that one.

279
00:41:28,486 --> 00:41:32,650
Have you already forgotten?
I remembered after seeing it once.

280
00:41:35,025 --> 00:41:40,224
- It's an F.
- Of course. That's what it is.

281
00:41:40,364 --> 00:41:45,028
What's wrong with my head today?
An F that's it.

282
00:41:45,169 --> 00:41:47,399
What do you think it's used for?

283
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:53,140
It's the first letter in F-ternoon.

284
00:41:53,878 --> 00:41:57,939
Of course. But you didn't
figure that out alone.

285
00:41:58,082 --> 00:42:02,075
- The teacher must have told you.
- No, I figured it out myself.

286
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:06,647
You did?
You're getting clever, Pelle.

287
00:42:07,091 --> 00:42:11,221
There's no end to what a lad with
so much book learning can do.

288
00:43:37,481 --> 00:43:41,815
Maybe we'll get roast pork
with raisins, Pelle.

289
00:43:43,053 --> 00:43:48,150
Or with apples. Some places
they make it with apples instead.

290
00:43:51,095 --> 00:43:52,392
We'll see.

291
00:43:57,635 --> 00:44:00,763
Get out! I don't want
any more trouble with you.

292
00:44:00,904 --> 00:44:05,841
- Get out!
- Oh, hell, herring on Christmas Eve.

293
00:44:05,976 --> 00:44:11,039
If you don't like the food,
then find some other place.

294
00:44:11,181 --> 00:44:14,150
Herring, herring ...
Herring every single day!

295
00:44:14,284 --> 00:44:17,253
Couldn't we have had
roast pork for Christmas?

296
00:44:17,388 --> 00:44:21,154
Damn you, always complaining.
Go back to Sweden ...

297
00:44:21,291 --> 00:44:23,156
... if you don't like it here.

298
00:44:23,293 --> 00:44:28,287
Are you so damn stingy? Don't
you think we work hard enough?

299
00:44:28,432 --> 00:44:32,528
And you, of all people, say that.
Go to your room.

300
00:44:33,570 --> 00:44:34,628
Damned!

301
00:44:35,239 --> 00:44:36,672
Damned!

302
00:44:42,012 --> 00:44:45,641
Damn the Stone Farm.

303
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:53,755
Does anyone else
have any complaints?

304
00:47:38,121 --> 00:47:39,315
Scram, you oaf!

305
00:47:39,456 --> 00:47:42,118
What are you doing here?
Go back to the other oafs.

306
00:47:42,326 --> 00:47:44,988
Watch out, Pelle. The water's wet.

307
00:47:45,128 --> 00:47:47,596
You could get wet, you yellow-belly.

308
00:48:07,351 --> 00:48:11,253
Get lost, Pelle! You could
get dizzy and fall in the water.

309
00:48:14,524 --> 00:48:16,287
Go home, Pelle!

310
00:48:19,062 --> 00:48:23,522
- Go back to the other oafs.
- Get lost, yellow-belly!

311
00:48:29,473 --> 00:48:30,906
Go home, yellow-belly!

312
00:48:31,041 --> 00:48:35,569
I'm no more that than you! You
don't even dare jump in the water.

313
00:49:47,551 --> 00:49:51,920
You must be crazy,
jumping into the water...

314
00:49:52,055 --> 00:49:54,148
... like some love-sick woman.

315
00:49:55,392 --> 00:49:58,953
A good beating is what you need.

316
00:49:59,162 --> 00:50:05,795
If you had drowned I'd have given
you such a beating, believe me.

317
00:50:05,936 --> 00:50:09,463
To think I should be the father
of such a half-witted idiot.

318
00:50:12,642 --> 00:50:16,669
Do you think, doctor,
he'd be better if you bled him?

319
00:50:32,429 --> 00:50:33,726
Here you are.

320
00:50:34,531 --> 00:50:36,396
This will help your cold.

321
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:47,443
Don't be afraid, Pelle.
I'm not a witch.

322
00:50:49,012 --> 00:50:52,880
Just very unhappy sometimes.

323
00:50:55,685 --> 00:50:57,482
Oh, dear Lord ...

324
00:50:59,689 --> 00:51:03,489
...you don't even have a mother,
poor thing.

325
00:51:04,561 --> 00:51:07,121
It's three years since
Mama Bengta died.

326
00:50:32,582 --> 00:50:33,879
Here you are.

327
00:50:34,684 --> 00:50:36,549
This will help your cold.

328
00:50:43,193 --> 00:50:47,596
Don't be afraid, Pelle.
I'm not a witch.

329
00:50:49,165 --> 00:50:53,033
Just very unhappy sometimes.

330
00:50:55,838 --> 00:50:57,635
Oh, dear Lord ...

331
00:50:59,842 --> 00:51:03,642
...you don't even have a mother,
poor thing.

332
00:51:04,714 --> 00:51:07,274
It's three years since
Mama Bengta died.

333
00:51:08,514 --> 00:51:11,677
She's lying in the left-hand corner
of the cemetery now.

334
00:51:12,785 --> 00:51:14,878
Do you miss her much?

335
00:51:17,690 --> 00:51:20,022
Lasse mends my clothes.

336
00:51:21,026 --> 00:51:23,654
She was a good mother
to you, wasn't she?

337
00:51:26,031 --> 00:51:28,727
She was so ill and grouchy
at the end.

338
00:51:29,235 --> 00:51:31,328
It was better that she died.

339
00:51:32,871 --> 00:51:37,968
But we'll marry again soon.

340
00:51:39,712 --> 00:51:41,543
And then you'll leave.

341
00:51:44,917 --> 00:51:47,249
You don't like it here anyway,
do you?

342
00:51:48,787 --> 00:51:51,347
Nobody likes it at Stone Farm.

343
00:51:52,157 --> 00:51:54,352
Everything turns bad here.

344
00:51:55,394 --> 00:51:57,521
It must be an old curse.

345
00:51:58,530 --> 00:52:00,395
Is that what they say?

346
00:52:01,433 --> 00:52:02,491
Well, well ...

347
00:52:05,337 --> 00:52:07,305
And what do they say about me?

348
00:52:09,141 --> 00:52:11,405
That Missus has a pact
with the devil ...

349
00:52:11,543 --> 00:52:14,068
... and turns into a werewolf at night.

350
00:52:17,750 --> 00:52:22,483
And just because
I love only one man.

351
00:52:27,726 --> 00:52:30,160
Why does he do this to me?

352
00:52:30,763 --> 00:52:33,891
He's gone into town again,
the lecher.

353
00:52:34,533 --> 00:52:38,128
I married him,
made him a proprietor...

354
00:52:38,871 --> 00:52:42,773
... gave him my love.
The best I have, I've given him.

355
00:52:43,375 --> 00:52:46,572
If only he could have
given me a child.

356
00:52:46,745 --> 00:52:50,909
- I think I'd better go down to papa.
- Now you're afraid of me again.

357
00:52:53,852 --> 00:52:55,843
You're a good boy, Pelle.

358
00:52:57,723 --> 00:53:02,854
If I had a son, I would
want him to be like you.

359
00:54:22,307 --> 00:54:26,437
Papa, there's the Missus
with her young family.

360
00:54:29,882 --> 00:54:32,282
Pelle, you step forward.

361
00:54:37,790 --> 00:54:39,553
Hello, Pelle. Where's your father?

362
00:54:45,264 --> 00:54:49,166
This is our stablehand, Lasse
Karlsson and his son Pelle.

363
00:54:49,301 --> 00:54:50,268
Hello.

364
00:54:54,206 --> 00:54:58,074
This is my niece from Copenhagen.

365
00:54:58,210 --> 00:55:01,077
Miss Signe is going to stay with us.

366
00:55:36,014 --> 00:55:38,073
I've forgotten what 2 x 2 is.

367
00:55:40,252 --> 00:55:43,221
Even if my knowledge
is somewhat rusty...

368
00:55:43,355 --> 00:55:45,653
... I'll see if I can help you.

369
00:55:46,492 --> 00:55:48,756
2 x 2 is 5.

370
00:55:54,900 --> 00:55:58,563
Which is lighter, a pound of
feathers or a pound of lead?

371
00:55:58,704 --> 00:56:00,729
Not you, Pelle.

372
00:56:02,574 --> 00:56:06,670
Perhaps Pelle would be so kind
as to repeat his question.

373
00:56:08,380 --> 00:56:12,339
If a pound of flour costs 12 øre, what
does a barrel of gunpowder cost?

374
00:57:13,145 --> 00:57:16,672
Where the hell's the herring?
That's all I ever eat.

375
00:57:17,783 --> 00:57:19,546
Herring, herring, herring!

376
00:57:20,285 --> 00:57:23,413
Do you know the difference
between you and a buttock?

377
00:57:24,756 --> 00:57:27,020
I don't know either.

378
00:57:28,860 --> 00:57:32,318
Erik, did you hear what I asked?

379
00:57:33,165 --> 00:57:37,033
Lasse, can you take my place
at the chaff-cutter tonight?

380
00:57:37,169 --> 00:57:38,864
But it's Saturday.

381
00:57:40,172 --> 00:57:42,140
I'm going out to have some fun.

382
00:57:43,809 --> 00:57:45,777
You're not getting off so easy.

383
00:57:52,484 --> 00:57:55,078
He's got a way with women,
like his papa.

384
00:57:55,220 --> 00:57:58,018
It must be a hell of a long time
since Lasse Karlsson ...

385
00:57:58,156 --> 00:58:02,286
Karna, I've been thinking lately...

386
00:58:02,427 --> 00:58:08,024
You've been good to Pelle,
and you like the boy.

387
00:58:08,233 --> 00:58:13,034
Why not move in together. We could
have a good life, the two of us.

388
00:58:13,505 --> 00:58:15,370
You're too old, Lasse.

389
00:58:15,507 --> 00:58:19,876
My man has to be dangerous.
You're not dangerous anymore.

390
00:58:20,345 --> 00:58:21,539
I see.

391
00:58:24,716 --> 00:58:27,207
So you're out fishing for young men.

392
00:58:28,253 --> 00:58:31,245
Watch out you don't miss the boat.

393
00:58:31,923 --> 00:58:35,256
Lasse, run down to the store
and get us some brandy.

394
00:58:35,827 --> 00:58:38,762
Come on, damn it. It's Saturday.

395
00:58:38,897 --> 00:58:43,129
You can get your own brandy.
Just because someone is old ...

396
00:58:44,102 --> 00:58:47,196
In the old days there was respect.
They always said ...

397
00:58:47,339 --> 00:58:50,069
... "Where's Lasse?
Get Lasse Karlsson."

398
00:58:50,809 --> 00:58:54,108
The girls were chasing you,
even if you were married.

399
00:58:54,246 --> 00:58:55,645
There was respect.

400
00:59:03,188 --> 00:59:04,348
Papa!

401
00:59:10,362 --> 00:59:13,160
I had hoped when we came here ...

402
00:59:13,298 --> 00:59:18,759
...that there would be some
money left to buy a little house ...

403
00:59:19,137 --> 00:59:23,574
... and maybe find a woman,
who could take care of us.

404
00:59:25,744 --> 00:59:29,976
Then we could have coffee in bed
Sunday mornings, eh Pelle?

405
00:59:30,115 --> 00:59:34,074
We could run away together, papa.

406
00:59:34,386 --> 00:59:35,648
Run away...

407
00:59:36,354 --> 00:59:40,188
But think of the authorities.
I don't want to become an outlaw.

408
00:59:40,325 --> 00:59:43,294
I mean far away, to America.

409
00:59:43,595 --> 00:59:46,826
We could go to America and
get us a house and a wife.

410
00:59:47,499 --> 00:59:49,694
We could save up
all our money, papa.

411
00:59:53,171 --> 00:59:54,433
We have to get away.

412
01:00:20,732 --> 01:00:22,427
What are you doing here?

413
01:00:29,541 --> 01:00:33,375
- Stealing eggs. I was so hungry.
- Don't tell anyone you saw me.

414
01:00:39,785 --> 01:00:41,878
I know who the father is.

415
01:01:00,238 --> 01:01:02,968
You mustn't tell anyone.

416
01:01:05,744 --> 01:01:10,681
H is father would ...
If he knew, he would ...

417
01:01:11,850 --> 01:01:14,375
I'm not good enough for them.

418
01:01:15,353 --> 01:01:17,878
I don't know what to do.

419
01:01:18,590 --> 01:01:20,285
Promise not to tell.

420
01:01:24,629 --> 01:01:25,857
Never.

421
01:01:39,311 --> 01:01:40,369
Pelle!

422
01:01:42,848 --> 01:01:43,906
Come here!

423
01:01:47,719 --> 01:01:50,950
- What were you doing there?
- Stealing eggs.

424
01:01:52,290 --> 01:01:53,348
Bend over.

425
01:02:41,673 --> 01:02:43,504
Can I have your half-crown?

426
01:02:43,675 --> 01:02:46,473
Have my half-crown?
Are you crazy?

427
01:02:47,345 --> 01:02:49,745
I'll need it when I go to America.

428
01:02:50,882 --> 01:02:53,442
When I'm bigger
I'll give you back ten.

429
01:02:53,585 --> 01:02:57,112
You'll never get big.
You're deformed.

430
01:02:59,891 --> 01:03:03,019
I'll go on show ... at tivolis.

431
01:03:04,462 --> 01:03:05,690
At tivolis?

432
01:03:05,830 --> 01:03:08,594
As a monster. I'll get filthy rich.

433
01:03:15,473 --> 01:03:16,599
But Pelle ...

434
01:03:19,444 --> 01:03:22,971
... give it to me and you can
beat me 100 times with nettles.

435
01:03:24,015 --> 01:03:25,505
On your bare skin?

436
01:03:26,551 --> 01:03:27,677
A hundred times.

437
01:03:28,853 --> 01:03:31,344
- You can't take that.
- As hard as you want.

438
01:03:41,132 --> 01:03:43,293
A hundred blows. Are you ready?

439
01:04:03,021 --> 01:04:04,318
That's enough.

440
01:04:06,958 --> 01:04:08,926
Then you don't get the money.

441
01:04:09,661 --> 01:04:11,390
You hit too hard.

442
01:04:13,298 --> 01:04:16,290
- You want it or not?
- The money first, then.

443
01:05:15,427 --> 01:05:19,124
Can't you tell us anything about
Adam and Eve and the serpent?

444
01:05:21,332 --> 01:05:22,299
Well?

445
01:05:23,334 --> 01:05:24,892
We're waiting.

446
01:05:27,138 --> 01:05:30,471
Have you ever heard of
Adam and Eve and the serpent?

447
01:05:34,579 --> 01:05:36,774
Haven't you been listening in class?

448
01:05:38,616 --> 01:05:43,644
What did the serpent promise them
if they ate from the apple?

449
01:05:49,160 --> 01:05:51,594
Don't think I feel sorry for you.

450
01:05:52,864 --> 01:05:58,894
It promised that if they could
distinguish between good and evil.

451
01:06:00,004 --> 01:06:02,768
How can we let you
continue in this class...

452
01:06:02,907 --> 01:06:06,206
... if you don't understand
the most elementary things?

453
01:06:07,145 --> 01:06:08,976
Are his parents here?

454
01:06:15,787 --> 01:06:19,917
They are not even here.
All right, sit down.

455
01:06:21,226 --> 01:06:23,524
Ne xt... Pelle.

456
01:06:33,071 --> 01:06:36,507
Perhaps you can tell us
what God said to the serpent?

457
01:06:36,975 --> 01:06:40,467
And God said to the serpent,
You shall ...

458
01:06:43,581 --> 01:06:47,039
You shall crawl on your belly...

459
01:06:48,686 --> 01:06:52,122
You shall crawl on your belly...

460
01:06:55,026 --> 01:06:59,122
- And does it still do so?
- Yes, because it has no limbs.

461
01:06:59,531 --> 01:07:01,965
And can you tell me what a limb is?

462
01:07:02,600 --> 01:07:04,591
A limb is...

463
01:07:06,804 --> 01:07:09,967
- A hand, for e xample.
- Yes.

464
01:07:10,375 --> 01:07:14,607
What distinguishes all limbs
from other parts of the body?

465
01:07:19,317 --> 01:07:21,808
A limb is...

466
01:07:23,855 --> 01:07:27,018
A limb moves independently.
An e xample?

467
01:07:37,368 --> 01:07:38,335
Ears.

468
01:07:39,337 --> 01:07:43,273
- Can you move the ears?
- Yes.

469
01:07:43,575 --> 01:07:45,975
I should really like to see that.

470
01:08:02,860 --> 01:08:06,956
So your ears saved you.
I always told you to use your ears.

471
01:08:18,443 --> 01:08:19,410
Rud!

472
01:08:27,619 --> 01:08:30,019
Rud, you idiot. Come back!

473
01:08:32,857 --> 01:08:38,295
If you run away you'll never get
to your grandma in heaven.

474
01:08:44,202 --> 01:08:47,069
You can have my knife
if you come back.

475
01:08:55,913 --> 01:08:57,938
You can't do that to me.

476
01:10:48,559 --> 01:10:49,821
What are you doing?

477
01:10:52,463 --> 01:10:55,955
Don't remove those stones.
The child is buried there.

478
01:10:57,835 --> 01:11:02,363
Yes it is... Anna killed your child
and she was sent to jail.

479
01:11:07,812 --> 01:11:09,279
I did it...

480
01:11:11,582 --> 01:11:13,550
I killed the child.

481
01:11:17,889 --> 01:11:20,255
Papa could never kill me.

482
01:11:28,666 --> 01:11:30,293
Why can't you leave me alone?

483
01:11:32,103 --> 01:11:36,130
It's my meadow, and you mustn't
take the stones away from the child.

484
01:11:37,608 --> 01:11:41,169
You mustn't say that.
You mustn't lie before God.

485
01:11:41,712 --> 01:11:44,510
The child is in the cemetery,
in consecrated earth.

486
01:11:44,649 --> 01:11:46,082
The child is buried here.

487
01:11:46,217 --> 01:11:49,118
I've seen his soul burning
on the rocks at night.

488
01:11:49,253 --> 01:11:52,313
That's because God won't
let him come up to Heaven.

489
01:12:28,125 --> 01:12:29,092
N ils!

490
01:13:01,259 --> 01:13:04,228
Who has gone out there
into the arms of death?

491
01:13:04,729 --> 01:13:08,392
It's N ils.
He went out with the line.

492
01:15:26,637 --> 01:15:29,629
Your eyes are young.
Can you see N ils?

493
01:16:22,126 --> 01:16:23,821
He was a good boy.

494
01:16:25,229 --> 01:16:27,322
He was my everything.

495
01:16:28,132 --> 01:16:31,431
My light... my warmth.

496
01:16:33,537 --> 01:16:37,166
He never spoke an evil word.

497
01:16:37,641 --> 01:16:40,610
Even though I denied him his love.

498
01:16:42,847 --> 01:16:45,372
Now I'm without a son.

499
01:16:46,250 --> 01:16:48,184
Without a child.

500
01:17:00,197 --> 01:17:06,102
May he find peace now.
He had so little of it here on earth.

501
01:17:09,073 --> 01:17:11,803
He rescued the lives of five men.

502
01:17:12,777 --> 01:17:17,544
Maybe now
Our Lord will receive him.

503
01:17:32,763 --> 01:17:35,323
Come on, Erik.
Come on!

504
01:17:36,233 --> 01:17:39,259
Two more inches and you've won
yourself a bottle of brandy.

505
01:17:48,179 --> 01:17:51,808
When will you drink it?
The Manager says you have to work.

506
01:17:52,550 --> 01:17:57,715
He can work if he wants,
the bloody Stone Farm manager.

507
01:17:57,855 --> 01:18:01,814
No one is going to keep Erik in,
when he's free and wants some fun.

508
01:18:02,526 --> 01:18:04,016
Can I come with you?

509
01:18:04,595 --> 01:18:06,825
Not now, Pelle.

510
01:18:08,365 --> 01:18:12,426
Not now ...
Remember in one year...

511
01:18:12,570 --> 01:18:17,769
When the snow melts, then we'll
go out into the real world.

512
01:18:18,209 --> 01:18:23,579
First to America and then
to Negroland and China.

513
01:18:25,182 --> 01:18:27,548
The whole damn world, Pelle.

514
01:18:44,301 --> 01:18:48,897
Where are you going?
You scoundrel! Erik!

515
01:18:52,576 --> 01:18:53,736
What's this?

516
01:18:53,911 --> 01:18:55,469
Are you ill?

517
01:18:55,613 --> 01:18:59,572
I must have caught a cold.
My whole body is shivering.

518
01:18:59,750 --> 01:19:03,015
It couldn't be mumps, could it?
Let's look at you, boy.

519
01:19:03,153 --> 01:19:06,054
Look at you, lying there
in your Sunday clothes.

520
01:19:06,190 --> 01:19:07,953
What's this, your funeral dress?

521
01:19:08,592 --> 01:19:11,493
Were you going out to buy
yourself a burial place, huh?

522
01:19:11,629 --> 01:19:16,692
It's about time we get you into the
ground. You're beginning to smell.

523
01:19:17,534 --> 01:19:19,434
I'm not dead yet...

524
01:19:21,105 --> 01:19:24,370
And I don't smell more
than some people.

525
01:19:27,177 --> 01:19:30,169
Always trouble with you.
Never satisfied with the food.

526
01:19:30,314 --> 01:19:33,283
- Always complaining about work.
- Why don't you hit me?

527
01:19:33,417 --> 01:19:34,509
Go on, hit me!

528
01:19:39,924 --> 01:19:42,518
There must be authorities
in this country.

529
01:19:45,195 --> 01:19:47,186
Now you do your job...

530
01:19:47,698 --> 01:19:50,258
... or I'll show you the authorities.

531
01:20:32,810 --> 01:20:36,246
The manager wants you to be quiet.

532
01:20:39,950 --> 01:20:43,681
What are you saying,
you little chicken?

533
01:20:45,422 --> 01:20:49,119
- The manager wants you ...
- I can't hear you.

534
01:20:50,728 --> 01:20:53,219
The manager wants you to be quiet.

535
01:20:54,531 --> 01:20:58,797
Listen to him.
Listen to that stupid boy.

536
01:20:59,069 --> 01:21:01,435
He is still wet behind the ears.

537
01:21:05,476 --> 01:21:08,934
Run back and tell him
to run his own errands.

538
01:21:10,447 --> 01:21:11,505
Skol!

539
01:21:19,056 --> 01:21:21,217
Skol, you devil!

540
01:21:27,231 --> 01:21:28,892
Good Lord ...

541
01:21:30,267 --> 01:21:32,201
I'm not dead yet.

542
01:22:55,986 --> 01:22:58,580
- Where are you going, Erik?
- To rest.

543
01:22:58,822 --> 01:23:01,689
- What?
- To rest.

544
01:23:02,826 --> 01:23:06,557
No. You have to do your job.

545
01:23:06,897 --> 01:23:11,163
- I'm allowed to rest.
- Who says so?

546
01:23:11,535 --> 01:23:15,528
- Like the others.
- That's for me to decide.

547
01:23:15,672 --> 01:23:18,004
Get back to work, Erik.

548
01:23:19,143 --> 01:23:23,512
- I always have to work.
- What a pity.

549
01:23:24,815 --> 01:23:27,375
That's because you're so clever...

550
01:23:27,518 --> 01:23:32,683
... and yell such loving words at me
when I turn my back.

551
01:23:37,628 --> 01:23:40,756
What the hell do you think
you get your money for?

552
01:23:41,098 --> 01:23:45,762
Are you so goddamn stupid?
You have to work for your wages.

553
01:23:46,370 --> 01:23:48,998
Get back to work...

554
01:23:49,273 --> 01:23:52,037
...you lousy bastard.

555
01:23:57,714 --> 01:24:01,912
I'll have to go to the authorities
and report you ...

556
01:24:02,052 --> 01:24:04,145
... and keep your wages.

557
01:24:04,288 --> 01:24:08,554
All your wages, Erik.
Fine.

558
01:25:14,858 --> 01:25:17,258
Papa! Lasse!
They're coming.

559
01:25:38,582 --> 01:25:42,143
Good Lord ...
They're going to do it.

560
01:27:02,632 --> 01:27:04,497
Carry him down to the cellar.

561
01:27:15,178 --> 01:27:17,373
Carry him down to the cellar!

562
01:27:29,292 --> 01:27:31,487
The rest of you go back to work.

563
01:28:41,665 --> 01:28:43,690
Come inside and get warm.

564
01:28:43,834 --> 01:28:46,132
I just wanted to get out of the wind.

565
01:28:54,344 --> 01:28:59,839
The mama Bengta died and now
she's in the cemetery back home.

566
01:29:00,851 --> 01:29:02,978
And your father is a widower?

567
01:29:07,491 --> 01:29:09,618
I think that's what it's called.

568
01:29:12,062 --> 01:29:16,021
The sea is hard. My husband's
been out there for a year now.

569
01:29:16,166 --> 01:29:18,293
I've been a widow since.

570
01:29:21,972 --> 01:29:23,564
Has he drowned?

571
01:29:26,209 --> 01:29:29,406
No, he hasn't.
I haven't had an omen yet.

572
01:29:41,191 --> 01:29:44,319
How long did you say
her husband has been at sea?

573
01:29:44,961 --> 01:29:46,451
A year, I think.

574
01:29:48,164 --> 01:29:50,632
So she's been alone a whole year.

575
01:29:52,102 --> 01:29:53,592
That's a long time.

576
01:29:58,942 --> 01:30:01,672
And you told her that
mama Bengta was dead?

577
01:30:02,612 --> 01:30:04,443
Yes, of course you did.

578
01:30:20,664 --> 01:30:24,122
This is all we have left
of mama's things.

579
01:30:27,404 --> 01:30:29,668
It's all or nothing now, Pelle.

580
01:30:31,308 --> 01:30:35,176
You go by Madame Olsen's place
after school tomorrow ...

581
01:30:35,312 --> 01:30:36,677
... and give her this.

582
01:30:38,548 --> 01:30:41,915
As a thank you for her kindness
to you in the storm.

583
01:30:49,693 --> 01:30:51,684
Would you believe it, Pelle ...

584
01:30:52,395 --> 01:30:55,626
... I got an omen last night
in that awful storm.

585
01:30:55,999 --> 01:30:59,628
I dreamt that a big black dog
stood at my bed.

586
01:31:01,438 --> 01:31:03,531
H is coat was dripping wet...

587
01:31:03,940 --> 01:31:07,535
... and I understood it had to be
the shipdog with a message.

588
01:31:07,677 --> 01:31:09,304
I got out of bed ...

589
01:31:09,613 --> 01:31:13,174
... and outside my window
I saw a ship go down.

590
01:31:15,185 --> 01:31:17,449
The heavens and the sea met.

591
01:31:19,422 --> 01:31:22,186
I saw my husband rise to heaven.

592
01:31:23,793 --> 01:31:25,988
He was completely transparent.

593
01:31:26,696 --> 01:31:29,631
Saltwater dripped off him.

594
01:32:03,466 --> 01:32:07,698
- Who's there?
- Pelle's father, Lasse Karlsson.

595
01:32:39,335 --> 01:32:40,859
So that's Pelle's father.

596
01:32:43,640 --> 01:32:45,699
It's quite a young son you have.

597
01:32:47,911 --> 01:32:49,845
Come in and sit down.

598
01:32:57,520 --> 01:33:01,354
He was a late-comer you might say.

599
01:33:05,762 --> 01:33:10,222
But I can still do a man's work,
both here and there.

600
01:33:11,634 --> 01:33:13,625
- Here you are.
- Thank you.

601
01:33:24,881 --> 01:33:27,679
I really ought to be going.

602
01:33:27,984 --> 01:33:29,178
Eat.

603
01:33:30,320 --> 01:33:34,154
Go ahead, eat.
That's how you know a man.

604
01:33:36,126 --> 01:33:37,821
You've walked a long way.

605
01:33:37,961 --> 01:33:41,294
I just wanted to thank you
for being so kind to the boy.

606
01:33:41,431 --> 01:33:45,367
Nonsense. Here ... eat.

607
01:33:49,072 --> 01:33:55,102
- You must have been a good wife.
- That's true enough.

608
01:33:55,945 --> 01:33:59,472
He got everything that was
his due when he was ashore.

609
01:34:00,083 --> 01:34:03,610
But he was ungrateful,
and one gets tired.

610
01:34:05,421 --> 01:34:09,016
I don't think mama Bengta
would have said that about me.

611
01:34:09,325 --> 01:34:13,455
There's plenty to do in this house,
if there's a man to help.

612
01:34:15,799 --> 01:34:17,562
I only have one cow ...

613
01:34:18,768 --> 01:34:20,929
... but one could have two.

614
01:34:23,006 --> 01:34:26,635
I'm only a poor devil
compared to you ...

615
01:34:28,278 --> 01:34:31,247
... but we have decent clothes.

616
01:34:32,115 --> 01:34:34,515
And I have a pair of good hands.

617
01:34:36,186 --> 01:34:40,122
- You're not afraid of lending a hand.
- No, I'm not.

618
01:34:43,126 --> 01:34:44,821
I'm not afraid of...

619
01:34:46,462 --> 01:34:49,954
... a cup of coffee in bed
Sunday morning either.

620
01:34:57,373 --> 01:34:59,671
Then I think I should have a kiss.

621
01:35:02,579 --> 01:35:04,979
Yes, you should.

622
01:35:20,597 --> 01:35:24,465
We must hope for happiness
and blessings for all three of us.

623
01:35:24,868 --> 01:35:27,462
You already like the boy.
I know that.

624
01:35:34,711 --> 01:35:36,872
You'd better stay the night.

625
01:35:44,254 --> 01:35:47,553
But I must be back
before the cows wake.

626
01:35:48,992 --> 01:35:51,085
And Pelle's all alone.

627
01:36:09,545 --> 01:36:10,534
Pelle ...

628
01:36:13,917 --> 01:36:15,316
Come on, Pelle.

629
01:36:19,055 --> 01:36:24,550
Everything's been arranged now.
We'll have a house and home.

630
01:36:25,028 --> 01:36:29,328
And a beautiful mother too.
Madame Olsen. You'll be happy.

631
01:36:31,734 --> 01:36:35,329
And maybe we'll get coffee
in bed Sunday mornings.

632
01:36:45,882 --> 01:36:49,784
Give us this day our daily bread ...

633
01:36:51,688 --> 01:36:54,088
Is that the book of biblical stories?

634
01:36:56,559 --> 01:37:01,428
Does it have the one about the man
whose sons pulled down his pants?

635
01:37:01,864 --> 01:37:06,233
- Noah?
- Yeah, old man Noah.

636
01:37:07,303 --> 01:37:09,965
- What did he drink, old man Noah?
- Wine.

637
01:37:10,406 --> 01:37:15,400
Was it wine? Then he must have
been a fine man, old Noah.

638
01:37:15,611 --> 01:37:21,208
Then there was the one about
the man who was so devilish clever.

639
01:37:21,351 --> 01:37:24,445
- Laban.
- Laban, of course.

640
01:37:24,587 --> 01:37:28,148
lmagine forgetting that... Laban.

641
01:37:28,825 --> 01:37:32,522
How was it now?
Could you have two wives then?

642
01:37:37,700 --> 01:37:40,567
The great prophets. Let me see ...

643
01:37:42,271 --> 01:37:44,671
lsaiah and Daniel ...

644
01:37:46,642 --> 01:37:52,080
I remember them. If you want to
you can ask me about the prophets.

645
01:37:52,915 --> 01:37:54,246
Okay, let's hear them.

646
01:37:54,417 --> 01:37:57,875
You better stop reading now.
Otherwise you may lose track.

647
01:37:58,021 --> 01:37:59,818
Of the four great prophets?

648
01:38:07,330 --> 01:38:08,558
Let's hear them.

649
01:38:09,365 --> 01:38:12,334
Well, first I have to make sure
I have them all.

650
01:38:14,404 --> 01:38:17,168
I don't understand
where they have gone.

651
01:38:17,306 --> 01:38:21,538
There's lsaiah ... and Daniel ...

652
01:38:25,982 --> 01:38:28,507
No, I can't do it today, Pelle.

653
01:38:28,651 --> 01:38:31,677
- Think of how old I am.
- lsaiah, Daniel ...

654
01:38:31,888 --> 01:38:37,155
lsaiah, Daniel, Jesus...

655
01:38:38,161 --> 01:38:41,221
No, not Jesus.
Of course not... Not him.

656
01:38:41,364 --> 01:38:44,765
They sure had devilish names.

657
01:38:44,934 --> 01:38:46,424
Try, papa.

658
01:38:49,472 --> 01:38:54,876
lsaiah, Daniel, Ezekiel ...

659
01:38:55,745 --> 01:38:58,009
- And ... and ...
- Jeremiah!

660
01:38:58,147 --> 01:38:59,705
And Jeremiah!

661
01:38:59,849 --> 01:39:06,015
lsaiah, Daniel, Ezekiel
and Jeremiah.

662
01:40:23,696 --> 01:40:25,536
Will you never grow up?

663
01:40:55,363 --> 01:40:58,662
Don't be afraid.
He wouldn't hurt a fly.

664
01:41:48,683 --> 01:41:51,117
Erik are you coming?

665
01:41:53,988 --> 01:41:55,683
To the fair, Erik.

666
01:41:59,494 --> 01:42:00,961
Come on, Erik.

667
01:42:03,264 --> 01:42:04,629
Come on!

668
01:42:07,969 --> 01:42:09,698
Come on, Erik.

669
01:42:13,474 --> 01:42:15,066
Isn't he coming?

670
01:42:18,012 --> 01:42:21,209
He can't stay alone here
without the manager.

671
01:42:23,685 --> 01:42:26,984
Can't you go get him?
You're the only one he Iistens to.

672
01:42:27,121 --> 01:42:29,817
Coming with us to the fair,
Erik old boy?

673
01:42:32,860 --> 01:42:35,727
Come on, Erik. Come on!

674
01:42:37,832 --> 01:42:39,857
Aren't you coming to the fair?

675
01:43:18,673 --> 01:43:22,734
lsaiah, Daniel, Ezekiel, Jeremiah.

676
01:43:22,944 --> 01:43:27,142
lsaiah, Daniel, Ezekiel, Jeremiah.

677
01:43:27,949 --> 01:43:32,613
Those were the days.
Imagine, two wives, Pelle.

678
01:43:32,754 --> 01:43:36,622
One could make coffee and
the other could mend and sew.

679
01:44:06,521 --> 01:44:10,958
Smile at the world,
and the world smiles back at you.

680
01:47:36,697 --> 01:47:38,221
What's going on here?

681
01:47:45,840 --> 01:47:46,966
I'm leaving, Aunt.

682
01:47:48,542 --> 01:47:50,772
But Signe, dear child...

683
01:47:53,614 --> 01:47:56,708
I don't really Iike Iiving in the country.

684
01:47:58,252 --> 01:48:02,882
I want to learn to take care
of myseIf. I've decided to...

685
01:48:03,290 --> 01:48:07,818
- You might have said something.
- I should have said it earlier.

686
01:48:07,962 --> 01:48:10,294
But dear child, I don't understand.

687
01:48:11,499 --> 01:48:14,195
I miss the city so...

688
01:48:15,169 --> 01:48:16,830
But I thought...

689
01:48:17,538 --> 01:48:21,235
Kongstrup and I were sure
you were happy here.

690
01:48:23,577 --> 01:48:25,169
Dear Signe...

691
01:48:26,080 --> 01:48:30,244
I'm sorry, Aunt, but I don't think...

692
01:48:31,752 --> 01:48:36,951
So suddenly. If you had said it
earlier I could understand.

693
01:48:38,025 --> 01:48:40,653
- Sorry, Aunt.
- But you might have...

694
01:48:42,463 --> 01:48:47,059
Why can't you look me
in the eye when we talk?

695
01:48:51,739 --> 01:48:53,969
How will you manage the trip?

696
01:48:54,942 --> 01:49:01,279
- And so suddenly...
- Kongstrup will take me to the boat.

697
01:49:01,415 --> 01:49:03,940
Oh thank God. I was so worried.

698
01:49:04,251 --> 01:49:08,881
If only I could understand.
We'II miss you terribly.

699
01:49:09,990 --> 01:49:13,187
I imagined Kongstrup and I,
we would sit here...

700
01:49:13,327 --> 01:49:15,921
...and watch you run
this glorious place.

701
01:49:16,063 --> 01:49:21,865
Signe, my dear, don't cry.
My dear...

702
01:49:22,436 --> 01:49:27,703
You can always visit us
whenever you want.

703
01:49:49,230 --> 01:49:50,697
Kongstrup!

704
01:49:52,166 --> 01:49:53,758
Kongstrup!

705
01:49:57,138 --> 01:49:59,299
Come out and let me talk to you.

706
01:50:01,709 --> 01:50:04,109
You owe me money, Kongstrup.

707
01:50:05,179 --> 01:50:06,441
Kongstrup!

708
01:50:25,933 --> 01:50:28,094
Miss Signe...

709
01:50:29,737 --> 01:50:31,637
Let me say hello to you.

710
01:50:34,175 --> 01:50:36,473
Are you too proud
to say hello to me?

711
